   |  BURN WATER!                                                           |
   |                                                                        |
   |  Join a secret organization of boat racing renegades and gear up for   |
   |  an aquatic adventure that will pump your adrenaline into warp speed.  |
   |  Hydro Thunder on Sega Dreamcast rips through eleven unique, visually  |
   |  stunning 3D tracks that are loaded with secret paths, ramps, hidden   |
   |  power-ups, special boat moves, roadblocks, and more. Based on the     |
   |  laws of Newtonian physics (a.k.a. gravity), boats handle choppy       |
   |  waters and high speeds with a realistic feel that will keep your      |
   |  white-knuckled grip fighting the controls. Navigate through wild and  |
   |  watery terrain as changing conditions challenge your cool. Race       |
   |  against your past record, or compete against other players and use    |
   |  hidden strategies to leave the salty dogs spluttering in your spray.  |
   |                                                                        |
   |  - Newtonian physics model emulates the feel of speedboat driving.     |
   |  - Total of 11 unique, visually stunning tracks.                       |
   |  - Total of 13 high-performance superboats: nine selectable and four   |
   |    secret.                                                             |
   |  - Boats range from V-hulls to high-concept prototypes, and offer      |
   |    distinct handling characteristics.                                  |
   |  - All boats are equipped with hidden boosters for added speed.        |
   |  - Loads of discovery challenges such as ramps, secret paths, hidden   |
   |    power-ups, special boat moves, and more.                            |
   |  - A perfect translation of the #1 arcade smash.                       |
